===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|then|then(ne)|lang=enm}}, {{term|than|than(ne)|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|þonne|lang=ang}}, {{term|þanne|lang=ang}}, {{term|þænne||then, at that time|lang=ang}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{recons|þan-|lang=gem-pro}}, {{recons|þana-||at that (time), then|lang=gem-pro}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{recons|to-||demonstrative pronoun|lang=ine-pro}}. Cognate with {{etyl|nl|-}} {{term|dan||then|lang=nl}}, {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|dann||then|lang=de}}, {{etyl|is|-}} {{term|þá||then|lang=is}}. Related to {{l|en|than}}.

===Adverb===
{{en-adv|-}}

# {{context|temporal location}} At that [[time]].
#: ''He was happy '''then'''.''
# {{context|temporal location}} Soon afterward.
#: ''He fixed it, '''then''' left.''
#: ''Turn left, '''then''' right, '''then''' right again, '''then''' keep going until you reach the service station.''
# {{context|sequence}} Next in order; in addition.
#: ''There are three green ones, '''then''' a blue one.''
# {{context|conjunctive}} In that case.
#: ''If it’s locked, '''then''' we’ll need the key.''
#: ''Is it 12 o'clock already? '''Then''' it's time for me to leave.''
#: ''You don't like potatoes? What do you want me to cook, '''then'''?''
# {{context|sequence}} [[at the same time|At the same time]]; [[on the other hand]].
#: ''That’s a nice shirt, but '''then''', so is the other one.''
# {{obsolete}} At the time that; [[when]].
#* '''1485''', [[w:Thomas Malory|Sir Thomas Malory]], ''Le Morte Darthur'', Book I.23, reprinted 1817, Sir Thomas Malory, [[w:William Caxton|William Caxton]], ''Morte Darthur: The Byrth, Lyf, and Actes of Kyng Arthur'', Volume 1, [http://books.google.com.au/books?id=eaUKAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA37&dq=%22the+knyght+sawe+hym+lye+soo+on+the+ground%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=rAgPT5-YI8O5iAeAobDgCQ&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=%22the%20knyght%20sawe%20hym%20lye%20soo%20on%20the%20ground%22&f=false page 37]:
